Sentencas: Effects of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical performance of DyBaCo2O5+delta (DBC), as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), was comparatively investigated.
Titulo: Influence of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical properties of DyBaCo2O5+δ cathode material

Sentencas: Powder samples were synthesized by EDTA-citric acid (EC) and ethanol supercritical drying assisted EDTA-citric acid (SCEC) techniques.
Titulo: Influence of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical properties of DyBaCo2O5+δ cathode material

Sentencas: The scanning electron microscopy (SEM) images show the particles synthesized by SCEC were smaller than those prepared by the EC method.
Titulo: Influence of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical properties of DyBaCo2O5+δ cathode material

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) value of SCEC-DBC as cathode was lower than that of DBC-EC cathode.
Titulo: Influence of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical properties of DyBaCo2O5+δ cathode material

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the single cell with SCEC-DBC cathode was higher than that of the cell with EC-DBC cathode in the investigated temperature range from 550 to 650 degrees C. (C) 2012 Elsevier Ltd and Techna Group S.r.l.
Titulo: Influence of ethanol supercritical drying treatment on morphology and electrochemical properties of DyBaCo2O5+δ cathode material
